# Scheme Modal — Implementation Guide

> **Purpose:** This document explains how the **Scheme Modal** (10+1 type scheme) works in the Sale Transaction & Modification modules, and provides a **copy-paste ready blueprint** to add it to any other module (Purchase, Challan, Credit Note, etc.).

---

## Overview

The Scheme Modal lets users apply a **"buy X get Y free"** scheme to an item row. For example, a **10+1 scheme** on a ₹100 rate item recalculates the effective rate as:

```
New Rate = (SchemeQty × OriginalRate) / (SchemeQty + SchemeFree)
         = (10 × 100) / (10 + 1)
         = ₹90.91
```

It also auto-calculates the **free quantity** based on the item's qty.

### Keyboard Shortcuts
| Shortcut | Action |
|----------|--------|
| `Ctrl+L` | Open scheme modal (from Qty or F.Qty field) |
| `Enter` on Scm(Qty) | Move to Scm(Free) input |
| `Enter` on Scm(Free) | Apply scheme & close modal |
| `Escape` | Cancel & close modal |

---

## Architecture — 4 Parts

The implementation consists of **4 independent parts** that must all be present:

```mermaid
graph TD
    A["1. HTML Modal Markup"] --> D["Working Scheme"]
    B["2. JavaScript Functions"] --> D
    C["3. Keyboard Handler Integration"] --> D
    E["4. Row Event Listeners"] --> D
```

