## Event Flow Diagram

```mermaid
sequenceDiagram
    participant U as User
    participant TS as transaction-shortcuts<br/>(capture phase)
    participant MH as Module Handler<br/>(capture phase)
    participant SM as Scheme Modal<br/>(inline onkeydown)

    Note over U: User presses Ctrl+L on qty field
    U->>TS: keydown event (capture)
    TS-->>TS: Not Enter key, skip
    U->>MH: keydown event (capture)
    MH->>MH: Ctrl+L detected on qty_X
    MH->>SM: openSchemeModal(rowIndex)
    SM->>SM: Show modal, focus schemeQty

    Note over U: User fills schemeQty, presses Enter
    U->>TS: keydown event (capture)
    TS-->>TS: schemeModal visible → return
    U->>MH: keydown event (capture)
    MH-->>MH: schemeModal visible → return
    U->>SM: handleSchemeInputKeydown
    SM->>SM: Focus schemeFree

    Note over U: User fills schemeFree, presses Enter
    U->>TS: keydown event (capture)
    TS-->>TS: schemeModal visible → return
    U->>MH: keydown event (capture)
    MH-->>MH: schemeModal visible → return
    U->>SM: handleSchemeInputKeydown
    SM->>SM: applyScheme()
    SM->>SM: closeSchemeModal()
    SM->>SM: setTimeout → focus free_qty
```

