## Quick Checklist for New Module

- [ ] **HTML**: Paste the Scheme Modal HTML markup (Part 1)
- [ ] **JS Functions**: Paste the `<script>` block with all 6 functions (Part 2)
- [ ] **Module Keyboard Handler**: Add scheme modal bypass check (Part 3B - ①)
- [ ] **Module Keyboard Handler**: Add Ctrl+L case in switch block (Part 3B - ②)
- [ ] **Row Event Listeners**: Add Ctrl+L handler to `freeQtyInput` keydown (Part 4)
- [ ] **No-Decimal Validation**: Add the capture-phase IIFE script (Part 5)
- [ ] **Verify**: `calculateRowAmount()` function exists in the module
- [ ] **Verify**: `showToast()` / `showAlert()` function exists in the module
- [ ] **Verify**: Row inputs use correct name pattern (`items[X][qty]`, `items[X][f_qty]` or `items[X][free_qty]`)
- [ ] **Verify**: Table rows have `data-row-index` attribute OR `id="row-X"` pattern
- [ ] **Test**: Open scheme modal with Ctrl+L → fill both fields → Enter → modal closes → focus returns to F.Qty
- [ ] **Test**: Qty=2.5, F.Qty=1.5 (sum=4) → allowed ✅
- [ ] **Test**: Qty=2.5, F.Qty=1.3 (sum=3.8) → warning on F.Qty, cursor stays ❌

