## Part 5: Qty + F.Qty Sum Validation

> [!IMPORTANT]
> Individual Qty and F.Qty fields **CAN have decimal values** (e.g., 2.5). But the **SUM of Qty + F.Qty must be a whole number**. If the sum is decimal, a warning is shown and the cursor stays on the F.Qty field.

### Behavior
| Scenario | Qty | F.Qty | Sum | Result |
|----------|-----|-------|-----|--------|
| Both whole | 10 | 2 | 12 | ✅ Allowed |
| Decimals, whole sum | 2.5 | 1.5 | 4 | ✅ Allowed |
| Decimals, decimal sum | 2.5 | 1.3 | 3.8 | ❌ Warning, cursor stays on F.Qty |
| Only qty decimal | 2.5 | 0 | 2.5 | ❌ Warning when leaving F.Qty |

### When validation triggers
| Trigger | Action |
|---------|--------|
| Enter on F.Qty | Check sum → if decimal, **block navigation to MRP**, show warning, cursor stays on F.Qty |
| F.Qty loses focus | Check sum → if decimal, show warning, **refocus F.Qty** |

> [!NOTE]
> Validation does **NOT** trigger on the Qty field's Enter (moving to F.Qty), because the user hasn't entered F.Qty yet. The validation gate is at F.Qty → MRP transition.

### Implementation — Capture-Phase IIFE

Place this inside the `<script>` block at the bottom of the module file (after the scheme modal functions):

```javascript
// Validate Qty + F.Qty sum must be a whole number — show error and keep cursor on F.Qty
(function() {
    // ADAPT THIS SELECTOR for your module's F.Qty field name
    const FQTY_SELECTOR = '#itemsTableBody input[name*="[f_qty]"]';

    function isFQtyField(el) {
        return el && el.matches && el.matches(FQTY_SELECTOR);
    }

    function getRowSum(row) {
        const qtyInput = row.querySelector('input[name*="[qty]"]');
        const fQtyInput = row.querySelector('input[name*="[f_qty]"]');
        const qty = parseFloat(qtyInput ? qtyInput.value : 0) || 0;
        const fQty = parseFloat(fQtyInput ? fQtyInput.value : 0) || 0;
        return qty + fQty;
    }

    function isSumDecimal(sum) {
        // Handle floating point precision (e.g. 2.5 + 1.5 = 3.9999999...)
        const rounded = Math.round(sum * 10000) / 10000;
        return rounded % 1 !== 0;
    }

    // 1. On Enter on F.Qty: validate sum before allowing navigation to MRP
    //    Capture phase fires BEFORE inline onkeydown, so stopImmediatePropagation blocks moveToNextField
    document.addEventListener('keydown', function(e) {
        if (e.key !== 'Enter') return;
        if (!isFQtyField(e.target)) return;

        const row = e.target.closest('tr');
        if (!row) return;

        const sum = getRowSum(row);
        if (isSumDecimal(sum)) {
            e.preventDefault();
            e.stopPropagation();
            e.stopImmediatePropagation();
            showAlert('warning', 'Qty + F.Qty must be a whole number (current sum: ' + sum.toFixed(2) + ')');
            e.target.focus();
            e.target.select();
        }
    }, true);

    // 2. On blur of F.Qty: validate sum and refocus if decimal
    document.addEventListener('focusout', function(e) {
        if (!isFQtyField(e.target)) return;

        const row = e.target.closest('tr');
        if (!row) return;

        const sum = getRowSum(row);
        if (isSumDecimal(sum)) {
            showAlert('warning', 'Qty + F.Qty must be a whole number (current sum: ' + sum.toFixed(2) + ')');
            const field = e.target;
            setTimeout(function() {
                field.focus();
                field.select();
            }, 50);
        }
    }, true);
})();
```

> [!NOTE]
> **Why capture phase?** The `document.addEventListener('keydown', ..., true)` fires **before** inline `onkeydown` handlers. When Enter is pressed on F.Qty with a decimal sum, `stopImmediatePropagation()` prevents the inline handler's `moveToNextField()` from ever executing.

### Adaptation Notes for Different Modules

| Module | `FQTY_SELECTOR` | Alert Function | Qty Field | F.Qty Field |
|--------|-----------------|----------------|-----------|-------------|
| Sale | `input[name*="[free_qty]"]` | `showToast()` | `qty` | `free_qty` |
| Breakage/Expiry | `input[name*="[f_qty]"]` | `showAlert()` | `qty` | `f_qty` |
| Purchase Return | `input[name*="[free_qty]"]` | `alert()` | `qty` | `free_qty` |
| Sale Challan | `input[name*="[free_qty]"]` | `showToast()` | `qty` | `free_qty` |

> [!NOTE]
> Purchase Return uses `purchase_rate` as the rate field (not `rate` or `mrp`), and row elements use `id="row-X"` with `input[name*="..."]` selectors instead of id-based selectors like `qty_0`, `rate_0`.

> [!WARNING]
> Do **NOT** auto-round or silently fix decimal sums. Show a warning and keep the cursor on F.Qty. The user must manually adjust Qty or F.Qty to make the sum a whole number.

